# Obsidian Vault Conventions

This document describes the structure and conventions used in this Obsidian vault for Claude Code integration.

## Directory Structure

```
PEOPLE/               # People notes with contact information
MEETINGS/             # Meeting notes organized by date
  └── YYYY/
      └── MM-Month/
          └── YYYY-MM-DD - Title.md

DAILY_NOTES/          # Daily notes organized by date
  └── YYYY/
      └── MM-Month/
          └── YYYY-MM-DD DayOfWeek.md

TEMPLATES/            # Note templates
  ├── Daily Note Template.md
  ├── Meeting Template.md
  └── People Template.md

SCRIPTS/              # Templater scripts (optional)
```

## File Naming Conventions

### People Notes
- Format: `First Last.md`
- Location: `PEOPLE/`
- Example: `PEOPLE/Jane Doe.md`

### Meeting Notes
- Format: `YYYY-MM-DD - Meeting Title.md`
- Location: `MEETINGS/YYYY/MM-Month/`
- Example: `MEETINGS/2026/02-February/2026-02-25 - Team Sync.md`

### Daily Notes
- Format: `YYYY-MM-DD DayOfWeek.md`
- Location: `DAILY_NOTES/YYYY/MM-Month/`
- Example: `DAILY_NOTES/2026/02-February/2026-02-25 Wednesday.md`

## Frontmatter Standards

### People Notes
```yaml
---
company: Company Name
location: City, State/Country
email: email@example.com
aliases:
  - Nickname
  - Alternate Name
tags:
  - People
created: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM
---
```

### Meeting Notes
```yaml
